-# Article picker for the claim-verification exercise: articles that prior
-# subject-matched courses worked on. The student picks one to see its claims.
-# Bracketed COPY notes are descriptive stubs, not draft text; titles are data.
.container.narrow.claim-verification-exercise.claim-verification-exercise--articles
  .claim-verification-exercise__intro
    %h1 Choose an article
  - if @articles.any?
    %ul.claim-verification-exercise__article-list
      - @articles.each do |article|
        %li
          = link_to article.title,
              "/courses/#{@course.slug}/verify_claim?article_id=#{article.id}"
  - else
    -# TODO: instead of a dead-end message, render an article-title input here so
    -# the student can choose an article themselves when none are suggested — so
    -# this empty case never strands them. (Tie in with the claim
    -# filtering/prioritization work.)
    %p.claim-verification-exercise__empty No articles available
